        "title": "Combining Strings In T Sql",
        "excerpt":"I found out the other day how to solve a problem that had been causing me issues when presenting data. I often got requests to resent data in such a way that we display information from a table in a grouped form while still allowing someone to consult all of the values relating to this grouping.   The solution isn’t very machine friendly and is end-user oriented. The code can be seen below:  SELECT      ta.a1,     ta.a2,     ta.a3,     ( SELECT            tta.a4,       FROM TABLE_A tta       WHERE            ta.a1=tta.a1            and ta.a2=tta.a2           and ta.a3=tta.a3       ORDER BY tta.a4       FOR XML PATH('')     ) AS a4plus FROM TABLE_A ta ","categories": [],
