        "title": "First Or Last In Tsql",
        "excerpt":"I’ve been looking for a while now to find a way to return just one row when the fields I am using split up my table return several rows per unique field combination. I found this little gem today:  Select     t1,    t2,    t3 From (    Select        t1,       t2,       t3,       row_number() over (Partition by t1 order by t1) rowrank    from tTable ) Where rowrank &lt;=1 This of course does not emulate first and last exactly as it doesn’t really allow you to influence the order of the returned fields in the partitioning. It is however very useful when you just want to return one value.  ","categories": [],
